computer typesetting of algol.wan application of computer-aided typesettingis introduced.  a working method is described for publishing algol by computerized translation fromhardware into reference representation, computerized planning of typographical lay-out and computerized controlof a typesetting machine.  the point is made that experts in science, technology, and programming areguaranteed a correct algol documentation without spending valuable time and power on typographic considerations and proofreading.cacm march, sydow, l. v.ca jb february ,   : pmb